This paper deals with the topic of internet censorship and the blocking of circumvention proxy servers. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves testing the reachability of these proxies from different locations, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper discusses the behavior of censors, which could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society). The paper also involves measuring the delay between the discovery of a proxy and its blocking, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper involves discussing the difficulties and opportunities for evasion in the context of internet censorship, which could be categorized under cs.SE (Software Engineering).
